<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-170-257 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 696 827</DOCID><JOURNAL>CSN  April 29 1991 n512 p2(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Troubled Syntrex goes on the block. (network integrator SyntrexInc.'s financial woes)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mehler, Mark.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Publicly held network integrator Syntrex Inc retains investmentbanker Broadview Associates to seek a buyer following huge lossesand a shortage of cash.andP;  Syntrex is the first major nationalnetwork integrator to be up for sale, which may set a newvaluation model for network integrators, according to analysts.andO;They contend that the acquisition of Syntrex would provide alarger company with a built-in technical infrastructure with whichto enter a market valued at $3.2 billion in the US and expected togrow 40 percent annually.andP;  Syntrex reported $51.1 million inrevenue for the nine months ended Jan 27, 1991, $27 million ofwhich was from services; the company lost $9 million in the periodand has lost $25 million since 1987.andP;  The recent losses areattributed by Syntrex Pres James Bruno to the company's 1990acquisition of Harris Corp's Lanier Business Systems Div and itsshift from proprietary to open systems.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Syntrex Inc. (Finance).andO;Ticker:    STRX.andO;Topic:     Computer Systems IntegratorsAcquisitionFinancial StabilityLocal Area NetworksComputer ServicesCompany ProfileLossesRevenue.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>